# OpenPill Static UI Standards

- Keep UX simple and progressive:
  - New controls should be optional and conservative by default.
  - UI must remain usable if optional backend features are disabled.
- Respect current style system:
  - Reuse existing color tokens and spacing patterns.
  - Keep additions visually consistent with existing cards/inputs/buttons.
- API wiring expectations:
  - Clamp and validate user inputs before requests.
  - Surface errors in user-facing text instead of silent failures.
  - Avoid introducing implicit auth assumptions; keep API-key behavior explicit.
- Search and retrieval UI:
  - Expose advanced options as opt-in.
  - Keep defaults aligned with safe backend defaults.
  - Prefer transparent labels (what a toggle does for the user).
- Maintainability:
  - Keep functions focused and avoid duplicated request logic.
  - Do not introduce external build tooling for this static page.
